== birth_of_peach_tree ==
You are born when a grain of pollen clinging to the leg of a honeybee falls into the open blossom of an ancient peach tree at the very back of an unkempt orchard somewhere in North America. As spring turns to summer, the petals of the blossom fall, and the fruit of a golden peach begins to swell in its place. You, fetus and seed, grow nestled in the center of the warm peach fruit, surrounded by sweet flesh. As summer passes, the fruit around you ripens. A child wearing a blue dress pauses while taking a shortcut through your orchard to contemplate the fuzzy golden fruit hangin just above her head. ->picking_peaches
